Tigers (initially titled White Lies) is a 2014 Indian-International film directed by Danis Tanovic, starring Emraan Hashmi. The film's music was composed by Pritam. It premiered at the 2014 Toronto International Film Festival. The film is based on a real-life story, about a salesman working the pharmaceutical industry in Pakistan, discovers its truths, while selling baby formula products, and tries to fight against the system.
The film is a joint production between Cinemorphic, French production company ASAP Films and Sikhya Entertainment.
